          "Mark on The Exam",
          "Overall Mark (0 to 100)",
          "492 students",
          "1 General Science Course",
          "Marks in Assignments and Exam",
          "[Assignment 1 Mark, Assignment 2 Mark, Assignment 3 Mark,\nAssignment 4 Mark, Assigment 5 mark, Exam mark] ",
          "After every moment of evaluation",
          "Authors perform a correlation analysis and identify Exam Grade to have a 0.72 correlation with the target variable.",
          "SVR\nELM\nXGBoost\nMLP\nExtraTrees\nGBoost\nDeep Neural Networks\nAdaBoost\nBagging\nLightGBM\nRandom Forest\nDT\n",
          "Holdout Method (64% train,  16% val and 20% test)",
          "{RRMSE: 0.37% - SVR Model 6 - includes all predictors, MAE: 0.268 - SVR Model 6 - includes all predictors, RMAE: 0.33% - SVR Model 6 - includes all predictors}",
          "Authors create 6 SVR models (one after eaxh moment of evaluation).\n\nAuthors examine two modelling frameworks. The first is sequencial: M1 refers to Assignment 1 and all subsequent models have the addition of the next assignment.\n\nIn framework 2, the authors start with Exam grade and start adding each assignment grade).\n\nAuthors do feature interpretation using LIME and SHAP and find that Exam is, unsurprisingly, the most important predictor of the final grade.\n\nEarly prediction is possible as early as Week 2.\n ",
          "Any model past Model 6 cannot be used for eacly prediction since it uses all elements of evaluation that are factored in to compute the final grade.\n\nModel optimization strategy and computyational cost of the techniques selected.\n\nNeeds additional predictors from other sources and generalization across institutions.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
